President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate Mark Acton as Commissioner of the Postal Regulatory Commission. Acton has been serving on the Postal Regulatory Commission since August 2006 and currently holds the position of Vice Chairman. Prior to his appointment, Acton worked as Special Assistant to the Chairman of the Postal Rate Commission, where he assisted in managing agency operations. He has a background in public policy, with over five years of experience handling legislative and regulatory concerns as Staff Director for the Republican National Committee Counsel's Office. Acton is an active member of the University of Louisville Alumni Association and the Kentucky Society of Washington. He holds a Master of Business Administration from the University of Maryland.